snippet: The Minnesota Orchestra said Monday that it was withdrawing from its two concerts at Carnegie Hall in November because it has not agreed on a new contract with its players.
abstract: Minnesota Orchestra says it is withdrawing from its two concerts at Carnegie Hall because it has not come to agreement on new contract with its players; old contract expired on Oct 1, 2012, and they have since been locked out.
lead_paragraph: The Minnesota Orchestra said Monday that it was withdrawing from its two concerts at Carnegie Hall in November because it has not agreed on a new contract with its players.

headline.main: Minnesota: Orchestra Cancels New York Concerts
headline.print_headline: Minnesota: Orchestra Cancels New York Concerts
